  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RUFI serving their refugee clients in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A large part of the clients of the Rural Finance Initiative (RUFI), a South Sudanese Microfinance institution, have fled to north Uganda. This grant helps RUFI to open a branch in north Uganda, enabling them to continue serving their clients.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RUFI targets 3 client groups: Self-Settled Refugees, Refugees in Camps and Local Ugandan people. South Sudanese refugees in North Uganda are denied financial services from existing MFIs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This grant helps RUFI to open a branch in north Uganda, to continue providing financial services to its clients who have fled from South Sudan and to collect outstanding loans from these clients.</narrative>
  </description>
